In this course the task of non-formal  and formal education  similarities and  differences will be studied, It deals with  non-formal science course planning in accordance with the laws and meaningful carrying out the course.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The general goal of the Supervising Science Related Activities in Non-formal Settings  Course is to develop students knowledge  and skills  for successful supervision of activities in non-formal  settings course.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course the student: 1. knows the similarities and differences of  non-formal and formal  education and  understand how to support student development; 2. is aware  of the laws that regulate youth-work in Estonia and is able to draw up a curriculum and action plan for non-formal science course; 3. is aware of the term "scientific literacy"  and is able  to support the development of scientific literacy with different teaching and learning methods  4. is aware  of the national curriculum  and is able to  support the development of general  and field specific competences with non-formal science course.
